channel.description:
This tutorial will teach you how to make a webclient. The revisions will be 317, 508, 562, and 637. For the 317 revision, this tutorial will focus on Delta and PI. For the 508 revision, this tutorial will focus on Berkyscape. Nothing has been found for the 562 revision, hook me up with a PM if you want to request one. For the 637 revision, I will be focusing on TorvaPkz v4. The reason these bases and revisions were chosen are because they are the bases that are most used. Sigh, here goes another 24 hours of my life.  :rolleyes:

[center][b][size=13pt]Tools that may be of use to you[/size][/b][/center]

[center][url=http://www.mediafire.com/?7q6fseyrzzr6bdl]JARMaker[/url][/center]
[center][url=http://www.mediafire.com/?vj3qh5m99j8jvih]WinRAR[/url][/center]

[center][b]Properly .JAR'ing the Client[/b][/center]

[b]1. [/b]
You're going to want to open up the JARMaker. Set the [b]Output File[/b] to the location of where you want the client to be .jar'd to. 

[IMG]http://i838.photobucket.com/albums/zz305/stuartperera/1.png[/img]

[b]2. [/b]
Next to, or under the [b]Output File selection[/b], you should see something like [b]application.jar[/b] or [b]demo.jar[/b]. Change that to [b]client.jar[/b]. 

[IMG]http://i838.photobucket.com/albums/zz305/stuartperera/2.png[/img]

[b]3. [/b]
Set the [b]Input File[/b] selection to where your .class files within your client are.

[IMG]http://i838.photobucket.com/albums/zz305/stuartperera/3.png[/img]

[b]317 - Delta[/b] The .class files are usually right with the .java files.
[b]317 - PI[/b] The .class files are usually right with the .java files or could be in a file called bin or data.
[b]508 - BerkyScape[/b] The .class files are located in the files folder along with the .java files.
[b]562 - ???[/b] Reserved
[b]637 - TorvaPkz v4[/b] Located with the .java files.

[b]4. [/b]
The next thing you are going to want to do is to click [b]Manifest Template[/b]. You should then see something like this. 

[IMG]http://i838.photobucket.com/albums/zz305/stuartperera/4.png[/img]

[b][size=9pt]Main-Class List (Note: These are Case Sensitive)[/size][/b]
[b]317 - Delta[/b] client
[b]317 - PI[/b] client
[b]508 - BerkyScape[/b] client
[b]562 - ???[/b] Reserved
[b]637 - TorvaPkz v4[/b] RunClient

You will then want to click Main-Class and type in what your base may be. (Another way to see what your main class is, is to right click your run.bat and would see something like 

[code=SYSTEM]@echo off
title Edge4Pk - Backup run
java -Xmx500m -cp .;Theme.jar client
pause
[/code] 
The [b]client[/b] is the main class so that is what you will need to set your "Main-Class" as.

After you set your Main-Class, click [b]Set Manifest[/b] and then click [b]Create JAR![/b]

The .JAR for webclients should be signed, so here are the steps to properly signing your client.

[center][b]Properly Signing the .JAR'ed Client[/b][/center]

[b]1. [/b] 
You should see some tabs that look like this,

[IMG]http://i838.photobucket.com/albums/zz305/stuartperera/5.png[/img]

Select the [b]JAR Signer[/b] tab.

[b]2. [/b] 
The first thing you are going to want to do is set the [b]Signed JAR File[/b] option to: [b]client.jar[/b]

[b]3. [/b] 
Your Jarsigner Location should be set by default, if it isn't click the button with the [b]...[/b] on it and find where your Java files are saved to. For Windos OS, it is usually "C:/Program Files/Java/jdk(Your JDK version here)/bin/jarsigner.exe"

[b]4. [/b]
Now click [b]Generate [u]K[/u]eystore[/b]. The Keytool Location should be set, if not refer to Step 3 and instead of [b]/jarsigner.exe[/b], it will be [b]/keytool.exe[/b] Instead of saving it as [b]keystore[/b]

[b]4. [/b]
As to where your Output Location was for the JAR'd client, set the Output Keystore Location to the same spot.

[b]5. [/b]
Keystore Alias, Public Key and Private Key should be written down or well remembered. Set it to anything AS LONG AS YOU REMEMBER.

[b]6. [/b]
You can just delete everything from Common Name through Province and select [b]Generate Keystore[/b]

[b]7. [/b]
Now you should select the [b]...[/b]button. Click that and where ever your Out Keystore Selection was saved to, select the keystore file and then click OK.

[b]8. [/b]
Now put in the information you wrote down at Step 5 for Keystore Alias, Public Key and Private Key. Then click [b]Sign JAR![/b]

