[center][b][size=13pt]317 - Project Insanity(Renamed)[/size][/b][/center]
[center][b](Just request if you want a named client tutorial to rename it.)[/b][/center]

Most released PI's nowadays have a built in renamed/ webclient ready client. All you have to do is change a few names, change a few links, add a few snippets, and change IP and port (If needed). So this will be the basic instruction on how to setup the basics for DSPK based sources (Like InsidiaX, HybridPvP, and ErasedPkz) aswell as FormationX Clients. The DSPK clients and FormationX clients are set up a differently so each step I will specify what to do for each client.

[b]1. [/b] 
You are going to want to find your link for your cache download. 

[b]FormationX:[/b]
Open up [b]client.java[/b] and search for 

[code=java]String url =[/code] 

You will find a method like this

[code=java]if (abyte0 == null) {
			drawLoadingText(15, "Downloading Cache");
			String url = "http://SERVERNAME.com/CACHENAME.zip";
			if (Math.random() > 0.5) {
				url = "http://SERVERNAME.com/CACHENAME.zip";
				System.out.println("Regicide");
			}
			downloadcache(url, "CACHENAME.zip", "", "CACHENAME");
			try {
				String s2 = signlink.findcachedir();
				File file = new File((new StringBuilder()).append(s2).append(
				"main_file_cache.dat").toString());
				signlink.cache_dat = new RandomAccessFile((new StringBuilder())
						.append(s2).append("main_file_cache.dat").toString(),"rw");
				for (int j1 = 0; j1 < 5; j1++) {
					signlink.cache_idx[j1] = new RandomAccessFile(
							(new StringBuilder()).append(s2).append(
							"main_file_cache.idx").append(j1)
							.toString(), "rw");
				}[/code]

Be sure to see the [b]SERVERNAME[/b] and [b]CACHENAME[/b] and change them to the proper names and links.

[b]DSPK:[/b]
You should have a class called [b]AutoCacheDownloader.java[/b] or [b]CacheDownloader.java[/b]. Open it up.

You should find a method like this right at the beginning of the class. 

[code=java]private String cacheLink = "http://SERVERNAME.com/CACHENAME.zip"; // Link to cache[/code]

Just within the quotation marks, set your new link to your cache.

